WEBVTT

00:01.001 --> 00:02.586
♪

00:02.586 --> 00:04.922
FRANK:
Previously on Hardy Boys...

00:04.922 --> 00:07.132
LUCY: I went into the woods
with Dennis that night.

00:07.132 --> 00:09.301
I broke up with him, and I left.

00:09.301 --> 00:11.512
I didn't want him
to remember everything.

00:11.512 --> 00:12.930
- You need to give me The Eye.

00:12.930 --> 00:15.307
The more you use it,
the more you're putting yourself

00:15.307 --> 00:16.642
and everybody you care about at risk.

00:16.642 --> 00:19.561
- What are you talking about?
- I am talking about Stratemeyer.

00:19.561 --> 00:20.562
They can trace it.

00:20.562 --> 00:23.315
- What's the matter, kid?
It's not what you were expecting?

00:23.315 --> 00:24.525
- You're a war hero?

00:24.525 --> 00:27.027
We found Dennis' tape.
It's really water damaged.

00:27.027 --> 00:28.237
- I can fix this.

00:28.237 --> 00:30.197
- I thought you had a date.
BRIAN: Yeah, I'm on it.

00:30.197 --> 00:33.367
Belinda, this is my friend Angela.

00:33.367 --> 00:35.577
- I've heard so much about you, Belinda.

00:36.328 --> 00:38.539
SAM:
McFarlane named his boat "Ellie."

00:38.539 --> 00:41.083
As in L-E. As in...

00:41.083 --> 00:42.751
FENTON:
Laura Estabrook.

00:42.751 --> 00:44.753
CALLIE: Okay. Here goes.
[clicking]

00:44.753 --> 00:46.797
[whirring]
He's being chased!

00:46.797 --> 00:49.049
- Dennis definitely saw
something he wasn't supposed to.

00:49.049 --> 00:51.635
JOE: What's that white thing beside it?
CALLIE: That says H2O2.

00:51.635 --> 00:53.428
That's hydrogen peroxide.

00:53.428 --> 00:55.639
FRANK:
Dennis saw someone making a bomb.

00:55.639 --> 00:57.391
There's going to be an attack
on Bridgeport!

00:57.391 --> 00:58.892
♪

01:00.602 --> 01:03.689
[insects chirping]

01:03.689 --> 01:06.733
[metal rattling, clicking]

01:06.733 --> 01:09.736
♪

01:09.736 --> 01:10.737
[click]

01:12.155 --> 01:15.158
[gate creaks, shuts]

01:15.158 --> 01:18.161
[water lapping]

01:22.875 --> 01:25.919
[dock creaking]

01:41.685 --> 01:44.688
♪

01:45.898 --> 01:49.610
[man struggling to breathe]

01:50.986 --> 01:52.613
- McFarlane.

01:52.613 --> 01:54.072
McFarlane!

01:54.072 --> 01:55.115
What happened? Hey.

01:55.115 --> 01:57.451
Hey! What happened?

01:57.451 --> 02:00.787
- [gasps] She... she knew.

02:01.496 --> 02:04.374
- Who knew?
[groaning]

02:04.374 --> 02:05.834
Who did this to you?

02:05.834 --> 02:08.337
Hey!
[groaning]

02:08.337 --> 02:11.340
[labored breathing]
[click, thud]

02:12.841 --> 02:15.344
- Keep it... safe...

02:20.349 --> 02:22.893
[truck rumbling]

02:23.644 --> 02:25.437
- McFarlane.

02:25.437 --> 02:28.815
♪

02:43.830 --> 02:45.958
[dial tone]

02:47.626 --> 02:49.711
[dial tone]

02:50.504 --> 02:52.631
[phone clicks]
SAM: Detective Peterson.

02:52.631 --> 02:55.259
- Hey, Sam, it's me. I'm at the marina.
McFarlane's dead.

02:55.259 --> 02:57.469
- I thought you were just gonna talk.

02:57.469 --> 02:59.471
- I didn't get the chance.
Someone poisoned him.

02:59.471 --> 03:02.057
- Get out of there. I'm gonna send
someone out to Gresham.

03:02.057 --> 03:03.475
- Thanks.

03:05.269 --> 03:08.272
[insects chirping]
[distant horn]

03:11.817 --> 03:13.527
[keys jingling, opens door]

03:13.527 --> 03:15.320
[distant horn]

03:15.320 --> 03:17.656
[sighs]
[shuts door, starts engine]

03:17.656 --> 03:18.740
[gun cocks]

03:18.740 --> 03:21.243
♪

03:21.243 --> 03:22.744
WOMAN: Drive.
[sighs]

03:24.371 --> 03:26.039
- Anywhere in particular?

03:26.039 --> 03:27.541
- Dixon City.

03:28.792 --> 03:31.211
- That's hours away from here.

03:31.211 --> 03:32.838
- Then we better get moving.

03:35.632 --> 03:36.675
[sighs]

03:37.509 --> 03:38.760
JOE: Now! No.
[VCR clicking]

03:38.760 --> 03:40.345
- I know.
[VCR whirring]

03:40.345 --> 03:42.556
- Stop! No...
- Joe, I know.

03:43.056 --> 03:45.100
[whirring, click]
JOE: There! No. Frank,

03:45.100 --> 03:47.102
pause it when the bomber
crosses the frame.

03:47.102 --> 03:48.478
- What do you think
I'm trying to do?!

03:48.478 --> 03:50.814
- Go frame by frame.
- I can't go frame by frame.

03:50.814 --> 03:52.524
JOE:
Wait, what's that blur? Is that new?

03:52.524 --> 03:55.444
- No, no, no, no. That's the hydrogen
peroxide again. Watch, Dennis zooms in...

03:55.444 --> 03:57.321
[whirring, click]
JOE: Okay, here comes the bomber,

03:57.321 --> 03:59.406
Frank. Be ready. It's fast.
[static]

03:59.406 --> 04:00.824
Come on, Dennis!

04:00.824 --> 04:03.076
- He ducks every time, Joe!
You know he ducks every time!

04:03.076 --> 04:04.703
- Yeah, but the bomber's about
to draw something!

04:04.703 --> 04:07.247
You don't have one more frame?
- I can't add a frame, can I?!

04:07.247 --> 04:09.416
- Well, maybe it's because
Callie spliced all of them out!

04:09.416 --> 04:13.045
- Hey, if it wasn't for me, you wouldn't
be watching anything right now! Stop!

04:13.045 --> 04:14.922
[click]
FRANK: Got it.

04:14.922 --> 04:17.299
♪

04:17.299 --> 04:19.468
What does that look like to you?
- It's a patch.

04:20.677 --> 04:22.471
For the school track team.

04:22.471 --> 04:24.515
The bomber is a Bridgeport student.

04:25.766 --> 04:27.809
- We have to get this to the police.

04:31.104 --> 04:33.690
[grinding, clicking]

04:33.690 --> 04:35.317
- What did you do?
- Hey, it's eating the tape!

04:35.317 --> 04:37.152
- It's all the splices you made!
One of them came loose!

04:37.152 --> 04:38.612
- Don't bang on it!
It was working just fine

04:38.612 --> 04:40.155
until Frank started cranking it
back and forth!

04:40.155 --> 04:42.783
- If I hadn't have cranked on it,
we wouldn't have seen what we saw!

04:42.783 --> 04:43.825
- Are you insane?!

04:43.825 --> 04:46.119
Do you have any idea what time it is?

04:46.119 --> 04:48.497
[heavy breathing] It's Demon Day,

04:48.497 --> 04:51.291
and I have to be up so early
to work on Vanessa's gown,

04:51.291 --> 04:54.419
so there better be a damn good reason
for all the yelling and banging.

04:54.419 --> 04:56.547
[heavy breathing]

04:56.547 --> 04:57.798
- Promise you won't be mad.

04:58.549 --> 05:01.552
- I don't look mad to you?
What is going on?!

05:02.845 --> 05:04.346
- You should've brought this
to me right away!

05:04.346 --> 05:05.848
- That's what I said to them.

05:05.848 --> 05:07.391
- You knew about this?
- Oh, uh,

05:07.391 --> 05:10.519
I knew they were investigating.
I didn't know, uh... Fenton wanted--

05:10.519 --> 05:12.271
- Fenton knew about this, too?

05:12.271 --> 05:14.273
[sighs]
You and I are gonna talk about this later.

05:14.273 --> 05:16.191
- We didn't know what was
on the tape when we found it.

05:16.191 --> 05:18.151
- Yeah, and we just...
We didn't wanna waste your time

05:18.151 --> 05:19.862
in case it was nothing.
- We just wanted to find out

05:19.862 --> 05:22.155
what happened to Dennis.
We didn't know we'd uncover a bomb plot.

05:22.155 --> 05:24.157
- That's not the point.
- Yes, exactly.

05:24.157 --> 05:26.785
That's what I said to them.
We're on the same page, you and I.

05:26.785 --> 05:27.995
- We're still going to talk later.

05:27.995 --> 05:30.581
This is my job. Trust me to do it.

05:30.581 --> 05:31.582
Okay?

05:32.583 --> 05:34.626
RILEY [on radio]:
We're bringing him in now, Chief.

05:34.626 --> 05:36.170
[radio static]
- Who are they bringing in?

05:36.170 --> 05:38.213
- Are you listening?
It's her job. Trust her to do it.

05:38.213 --> 05:40.090
- We're just trying to help.
JESSE: I don't need it.

05:40.090 --> 05:41.258
The bomb's been found.

05:41.258 --> 05:42.593
- What? How?

05:42.593 --> 05:44.761
[phone ringing]
[police station chatter]

05:44.761 --> 05:47.014
- We got an anonymous tip
about a suspicious package

05:47.014 --> 05:48.682
being loaded into a parked car.

05:48.682 --> 05:51.476
The suspect's in custody.
- Who is it?

05:51.476 --> 05:53.937
- I'm going to hang on to this,
in case we need it for evidence,

05:53.937 --> 05:55.731
if we can't get a confession out of him.

05:55.731 --> 05:56.732
- Out of who?!

05:56.732 --> 05:58.192
Who's the bomber?!
- Suspect!

05:58.192 --> 05:59.526
JOE:
Well, who is it?!

05:59.526 --> 06:01.737
TRUDY: You know what? I'll come
with you so we can talk about this.

06:01.737 --> 06:02.988
How mad are you?

06:02.988 --> 06:04.531
- Tom Elroy?

06:04.531 --> 06:07.534
♪

06:09.286 --> 06:11.788
[high-pitched ringing]

06:11.788 --> 06:12.789
♪

06:12.789 --> 06:14.416
[match strike, flame crackling]

06:15.667 --> 06:17.002
[quiet chatter]

06:18.003 --> 06:19.338
- Beautiful portrait, isn't it?

06:20.464 --> 06:21.798
And the perfect frame.

06:23.926 --> 06:25.135
♪

06:25.135 --> 06:26.720
[gasps]
[phones ringing]

06:26.720 --> 06:29.014
- Tom Elroy is being framed.

06:29.014 --> 06:31.266
We need to find the real bomber
before it's too late.

06:33.018 --> 06:36.021
♪ theme music ♪

06:46.323 --> 06:48.867
[birds chirping]

06:48.867 --> 06:51.870
[door creaks, shuts]
[radio playing]

06:52.913 --> 06:54.122
[plate clinking]

06:54.122 --> 06:57.417
- You know, I'm not sure what all
the sad faces are about.

06:58.377 --> 07:00.963
The suspect's in custody
Isn't that what you wanted?

07:00.963 --> 07:03.507
- It wasn't him.

07:03.507 --> 07:06.802
- Okay, well, let's just let Jesse
and the police worry about that.

07:06.802 --> 07:09.972
WILT: Okay. Black coffee
and a burrito to go. On the house.

07:09.972 --> 07:12.850
Happy Demon Day. Hm.
- Thanks, Wilt.

07:13.642 --> 07:15.644
I'll see you later.
- You're leaving?

07:15.644 --> 07:17.938
- Yeah. Mayor Krassner
has to sign off on the gown,

07:17.938 --> 07:20.274
which means I actually need to finish it.

07:22.109 --> 07:23.986
It's been a long night. Just...

07:23.986 --> 07:27.406
get some food and some rest,
and I'll see you at the parade.

07:27.406 --> 07:29.157
- See you there.

07:30.242 --> 07:31.243
[door bell jingling]

07:32.578 --> 07:34.329
[door shuts]

07:34.329 --> 07:36.498
- There is no way Tom is the bomber.
We need to figure out

07:36.498 --> 07:38.125
who's actually behind this.
JOE: It's got to be

07:38.125 --> 07:40.127
the guy that attacked me for the tape.
BIFF: He was wearing

07:40.127 --> 07:41.795
a mask, right?
How do we know it wasn't Tom?

07:41.795 --> 07:44.715
- Why do you always do this?
- Devil's advocate.

07:44.715 --> 07:46.216
We can't just be gung ho all the time.

07:46.216 --> 07:48.177
CALLIE: If Tom really is the bomber--
- He isn't.

07:48.177 --> 07:50.137
- But if he is,
he's already in custody.

07:50.137 --> 07:52.139
So, let's work another angle.
- Okay, but what if it's Tom?

07:52.139 --> 07:53.640
- Seriously? An anonymous tip?

07:53.640 --> 07:55.475
A bomb in the trunk of a car
that doesn't run?

07:55.475 --> 07:58.645
- Okay, fine. Who else do we know with
a military history and a hunting shack

07:58.645 --> 08:00.439
full of bombing materials?
- He's a patsy!

08:00.439 --> 08:02.941
The whole thing's been set up
to look like Tom finally snapped

08:02.941 --> 08:04.735
after all the nasty nicknames and rumors.

08:04.735 --> 08:06.361
Like the Demon Helper
was pushed to his limit,

08:06.361 --> 08:07.863
and he's getting his revenge on Demon Day.

08:07.863 --> 08:10.532
- Why would someone frame him
before the bomb goes off?

08:10.532 --> 08:13.202
♪

08:13.202 --> 08:14.703
- Because we were getting too close.

08:16.413 --> 08:17.873
Whoever it is is buying time.

08:17.873 --> 08:19.541
If the cops think that
they have the bomber,

08:19.541 --> 08:21.043
the real attack goes off without a hitch.

08:21.043 --> 08:23.337
- Is it really so hard to believe
my mom got the right guy?

08:23.337 --> 08:25.214
- It's not about your mom, Biff.

08:25.214 --> 08:27.382
Okay, she's following
the evidence that she has.

08:27.382 --> 08:30.427
But we saw clues off the videotape
that she didn't.

08:30.427 --> 08:31.762
Like someone on the school track team

08:31.762 --> 08:35.307
that was in Tom Elroy's shack with a map
of town and bomb-making materials.

08:35.307 --> 08:36.808
- Including fireworks.

08:38.685 --> 08:41.104
What if the real attack is happening
at the Demon Day fireworks tonight?

08:41.104 --> 08:43.273
- It'd be easy to disguise
a pipe bomb as fireworks.

08:43.273 --> 08:44.942
- Wouldn't it be easier
to use sticks of dynamite?

08:44.942 --> 08:46.860
- Where would a high school student
get sticks of dynamite?

08:46.860 --> 08:50.781
- Guys, stop. A pipe full of flour and
hydrogen peroxide is basically dynamite.

08:50.781 --> 08:53.492
Once it ignites an oxidizes,
it's real bad.

08:53.492 --> 08:54.952
Surround that with fireworks and...

08:55.786 --> 08:58.997
Way worse.
- We need to shut down Demon Day.

08:58.997 --> 09:00.624
- Absolutely not.

09:00.624 --> 09:02.501
[band practicing]
[crowd chatter]

09:02.501 --> 09:04.920
- Why? You said come
and see you if we need anything.

09:04.920 --> 09:06.296
- I was being congenial.

09:06.296 --> 09:09.967
Come see me for a tour of City Hall
or a fun campaign lanyard,

09:09.967 --> 09:11.760
not with some unsubstantiated theory

09:11.760 --> 09:13.720
that's going to cause mass panic
and ruin Demon Day.

09:13.720 --> 09:16.473
- Yeah well, an explosion at the fireworks
show'll put a real damper on things, too.

09:16.473 --> 09:18.350
- Listen, kids.

09:18.350 --> 09:21.311
The suspicious device has been
safely recovered and disposed of.

09:21.311 --> 09:23.689
The suspect is in custody.
- We don't think he did it.

09:23.689 --> 09:25.065
- That's nice. Can you prove it?

09:25.774 --> 09:26.775
- Not yet.

09:26.775 --> 09:29.111
- Then the festivities
will go on as planned.

09:29.111 --> 09:32.030
People come from all over
to see the Demon Queen

09:32.030 --> 09:33.615
and the parade and the fireworks.

09:33.615 --> 09:36.451
The money we make off parking alone
is enough to pay for the whole shebang.

09:36.451 --> 09:38.078
We simply can't afford to cancel.

09:38.078 --> 09:40.205
- I thought safety was your top priority.

09:40.205 --> 09:43.500
- It is, and the economy
and tough on crime.

09:43.500 --> 09:45.919
- It's not tough on crime
if you lock up an innocent person.

09:45.919 --> 09:47.421
- You're putting money
above public interest.

09:47.421 --> 09:49.715
- I'm making morale a top priority.

09:49.715 --> 09:50.883
- You can't have four top priorities.

09:50.883 --> 09:54.011
- It's a complex platform.
I don't expect you to understand.

09:54.011 --> 09:56.305
Look, why don't you
leave the politics to me,

09:56.305 --> 09:58.223
and the detective work
to the police, okay?

09:58.223 --> 10:00.142
The town needs this.

10:00.142 --> 10:02.311
The mine collapse,
the Estabrook scandal,

10:02.311 --> 10:04.813
now a missing-turned-catatonic kid?

10:04.813 --> 10:07.774
- The people of Bridgeport
want to exorcise

10:07.774 --> 10:09.943
those demons on Demon Day.

10:09.943 --> 10:11.820
- That's--
- It is time to celebrate,

10:11.820 --> 10:13.989
and what better cause for celebration

10:13.989 --> 10:16.533
than thwarting an attack
on this great town.

10:16.533 --> 10:19.494
We are done here. Happy Demon Day.

10:19.494 --> 10:22.497
♪

10:24.917 --> 10:28.128
- Okay, are you at least trying
to salvage the videotape?

10:28.128 --> 10:31.548
- If we can prove that Tom's not
the bomber, that there's still some risk--

10:31.548 --> 10:34.259
- Guys, enough! This is police work!

10:34.259 --> 10:35.594
It's serious, and it's dangerous,

10:35.594 --> 10:37.679
and I can't have you involved
any more than you already are.

10:37.679 --> 10:38.889
- We've got a development.

10:38.889 --> 10:40.724
- Did Elroy confess?
RILEY: No.

10:40.724 --> 10:42.976
- He says the only person
he'll talk to is Frank Hardy.

10:42.976 --> 10:44.394
- He must be confused.

10:44.394 --> 10:46.855
Does he mean Fenton Hardy?
The private detective?

10:46.855 --> 10:49.316
- No, he means the kid.

10:53.111 --> 10:54.363
Stop smiling.

10:54.947 --> 10:56.114
You're not going in there.

10:56.114 --> 10:59.034
♪

10:59.034 --> 11:00.953
It's not going to happen.

11:00.953 --> 11:01.954
[door opens]

11:06.583 --> 11:08.710
- I said alone.
JESSE: Don't push it.

11:11.505 --> 11:13.215
- Why'd you want to talk to me, Tom?

11:13.215 --> 11:15.175
- I trust you.

11:15.175 --> 11:17.719
Everything I say to them
falls on the deaf ears of dumb cops

11:17.719 --> 11:18.971
trying to coerce a confession.

11:19.680 --> 11:22.850
- Just trying to get to the truth, Tom.
- You work for the mayor.

11:23.851 --> 11:26.353
Krassner's been after
my land for years.

11:26.353 --> 11:28.021
If I go to jail,
he gets what he wants.

11:31.608 --> 11:33.694
- So, you think Mayor Krassner's
involved in this?

11:33.694 --> 11:35.404
- All I know is I didn't do this.

11:35.404 --> 11:37.197
I wouldn't build a bomb like that.
FRANK: Right,

11:37.197 --> 11:38.991
I believe you.
I know you wouldn't hurt anyone.

11:38.991 --> 11:41.159
ELROY: I appreciate it, kid.
That's not what I'm saying.

11:41.159 --> 11:43.829
I'm saying I wouldn't
build a bomb like that.

11:43.829 --> 11:44.705
♪

11:44.705 --> 11:46.540
I have experience with explosives.

11:46.540 --> 11:48.667
C4, blasting caps, det cord.

11:48.667 --> 11:50.210
The real stuff.

11:50.210 --> 11:51.879
The device that was found in my car

11:51.879 --> 11:55.757
was made with flour and
hydrogen peroxide and fireworks fuses.

11:55.757 --> 11:58.010
It's textbook anarchist stuff.

11:58.010 --> 11:59.511
- Something an amateur would make.

12:00.429 --> 12:02.472
- The only hitch is
the hydrogen peroxide.

12:02.472 --> 12:03.974
It has to be a high concentration,

12:03.974 --> 12:06.435
and it ain't easy to get.
Has to come from a lab.

12:07.144 --> 12:09.271
Military, pharmaceutical.

12:09.938 --> 12:12.900
What about a high school chemistry lab?
ELROY: Maybe.

12:13.692 --> 12:15.194
There's something else.

12:16.445 --> 12:18.906
There was somebody on my property
the other night by my car.

12:19.531 --> 12:21.241
Noise woke me up.

12:21.241 --> 12:23.202
Never seen them before,
but they weren't a student.

12:23.202 --> 12:25.662
- What did they look like?
ELROY: Sketchy.

12:25.662 --> 12:28.749
Had his hood up, full beard,
was wearing sunglasses,

12:28.749 --> 12:30.375
looked like somebody busted up his face.

12:30.375 --> 12:32.878
♪

12:32.878 --> 12:34.796
- It's JB in disguise, okay?

12:34.796 --> 12:37.132
He was spying on us at the movies.

12:37.132 --> 12:39.092
I broke his sunglasses when I punched him.

12:39.092 --> 12:40.511
- Y-you punched him?

12:40.511 --> 12:42.638
- JB's still in town?
BIFF: What do you mean still?

12:42.638 --> 12:45.140
I thought he was in hiding.
- No, he's staying at the motel,

12:45.140 --> 12:47.601
and he's working for Stratemeyer Global.

12:47.601 --> 12:49.478
They're not just a mining company.

12:50.020 --> 12:51.063
They're here for The Eye.

12:51.063 --> 12:53.190
- Again with The Eye.
I thought we were done with all that.

12:53.190 --> 12:55.275
- So, what, they still think
it's magic or something?

12:55.275 --> 12:56.527
- No, it's not.
It's impossible. It can't be.

12:56.527 --> 12:57.861
It definitely isn't.

12:57.861 --> 12:59.071
So anyways, why do we think...

12:59.071 --> 13:00.864
why-why are Stratemeyer spying on us?

13:01.573 --> 13:02.783
- They think...

13:02.783 --> 13:04.660
They think Joe
and I have The Eye.

13:04.660 --> 13:05.661
- Why?

13:05.661 --> 13:07.579
FRANK:
Because before the chamber collapsed,

13:07.579 --> 13:10.290
we were the last ones in there.
I was the last one to touch it.

13:10.290 --> 13:11.959
They think I swapped it out
for a fake.

13:11.959 --> 13:13.085
- Did you?
FRANK: No!

13:13.085 --> 13:15.295
I don't want The Eye. I don't want
anything to do with The Eye.

13:15.295 --> 13:16.547
Okay? It's nothing but trouble.

13:16.547 --> 13:18.966
- And when exactly were you gonna
tell the rest of us any of this?

13:19.758 --> 13:21.677
- You really want to talk
about keeping secrets right now?

13:21.677 --> 13:23.053
- Ooh, troubles in paradise.
- Zip it, Phil.

13:23.053 --> 13:24.513
- Shut up, Phil.

13:24.513 --> 13:26.014
- So, what other secrets
have you been hiding?

13:26.014 --> 13:28.350
- Focus! We have a lot of threads
to follow, and not a lot of time.

13:28.350 --> 13:30.185
FRANK:
We've got to divide and conquer.

13:30.185 --> 13:31.520
I'll go talk to JB,

13:31.520 --> 13:33.522
figure out how he's involved in all this.
- I'll go with you.

13:33.522 --> 13:35.566
- Really? What about the Lucy angle?

13:35.566 --> 13:36.984
♪

13:36.984 --> 13:38.068
- There is no Lucy angle.

13:38.068 --> 13:39.862
- Since when?

13:39.862 --> 13:41.113
She didn't want you questioning Dennis,

13:41.113 --> 13:42.656
she lied about being
with him in the woods,

13:42.656 --> 13:44.992
and she was the last person
to have his notebook.

13:44.992 --> 13:45.951
Show him, Phil.

13:45.951 --> 13:47.452
- Oh. Yeah, here.

13:47.452 --> 13:49.621
So, I found this
in Dennis' notebook.

13:49.621 --> 13:51.164
It was a lightning bolt
that was circled.

13:51.832 --> 13:52.833
I don't know what it means,

13:52.833 --> 13:55.085
but I think that's why
he got attacked again.

13:55.085 --> 13:57.212
BIFF:
Lucy had means and an opportunity.

13:57.212 --> 13:58.714
Plus, she's on the track team.

13:59.506 --> 14:00.674
- Now we gotta think of the motive.

14:00.674 --> 14:03.343
- Guys. Come on!
Th-there's no motive.

14:03.343 --> 14:04.636
Okay? She's on the junior team.

14:04.636 --> 14:07.806
The patch for the logo of
the junior team is white on blue.

14:07.806 --> 14:10.934
The patch we saw in the video
is-is blue on white.

14:10.934 --> 14:12.978
We're looking for someone
on the senior team.

14:12.978 --> 14:15.439
- Oh, okay.
Well, I didn't see the video, so...

14:15.439 --> 14:17.316
JOE:
So, she's not a suspect anymore.

14:17.900 --> 14:20.235
Got it?
PHIL: Got it.

14:20.235 --> 14:22.613
- I'm going with Frank.
- You should still talk to Lucy though.

14:22.613 --> 14:25.115
She could tell us who's on
the senior track team. I'll go with Biff.

14:25.115 --> 14:27.117
- Okay, and I'll dig into
the hydrogen peroxide.

14:27.117 --> 14:28.493
I take chem with Mr. Johnson.

14:28.493 --> 14:30.787
- Soon as you guys get the names of
everyone on the senior track team,

14:30.787 --> 14:33.498
we'll cross-reference with senior chem
and narrow down a suspect.

14:33.498 --> 14:36.627
- Which brings us back to motive.
JOE: No, there's no time for motive.

14:36.627 --> 14:38.170
Someone's going to blow up Demon Day.

14:38.170 --> 14:40.464
- Okay, so we got to ask why?
JOE: No!

14:40.464 --> 14:42.633
The real question is, where's the bomb?

14:42.633 --> 14:44.635
Could be with the fireworks, right?
Go check the fireworks.

14:45.135 --> 14:48.597
- Copy that. I'll go to the staging area
and do some behind-the-scenes filming,

14:48.597 --> 14:51.350
and if I catch anyone being suspicious,
I can ask them what their motivation--

14:51.350 --> 14:52.768
- No! Phil!
PHIL: I'm just saying,

14:52.768 --> 14:54.561
if motive is a concern... Is it a concern?

14:54.561 --> 14:57.231
- Just... don't draw...

14:57.231 --> 14:59.566
any attention to yourself.

14:59.566 --> 15:01.151
Okay? J-just...
[sighs]

15:01.151 --> 15:03.070
snoop around.
- Okay.

15:03.070 --> 15:06.073
We meet back here in an hour. Let's go.

15:06.698 --> 15:07.908
[birds chirping]

15:07.908 --> 15:10.035
- Why didn't you tell me
JB was still in town?

15:10.035 --> 15:12.412
- Slipped my mind.
- Really?

15:12.412 --> 15:13.914
'Cause it's kind of important.

15:13.914 --> 15:15.916
- There's kind of a lot
going on right now.

15:17.709 --> 15:20.087
- Sure this is it?
- Yeah, this is it.

15:21.713 --> 15:24.508
When we were fighting,
his room key fell out of his pocket.

15:24.508 --> 15:25.801
Room two.

15:25.801 --> 15:27.302
- You know, I don't get it.

15:27.302 --> 15:29.012
Why is JB working for
Stratemeyer anyway?

15:29.012 --> 15:30.681
After everything
we went through last year,

15:30.681 --> 15:32.516
I thought we were friends.

15:33.308 --> 15:35.394
- There's something else
I forgot to tell you.

15:35.394 --> 15:38.272
JB said that Stratemeyer
had a way of tracking The Eye.

15:38.272 --> 15:39.648
He said if we use it, they'll know.

15:39.648 --> 15:41.108
- It's got to be a bluff.

15:41.650 --> 15:42.860
- What if it isn't?

15:42.860 --> 15:44.945
- He's just trying to scare you
into handing it over.

15:44.945 --> 15:46.822
Look, if they could track it,
they'd come get it.

15:46.822 --> 15:47.948
- Yeah.

15:51.994 --> 15:53.370
♪

15:53.370 --> 15:54.496
FRANK:
Oh.

15:55.581 --> 15:57.082
Sorry. Wrong room.

15:57.082 --> 15:58.709
- No, you've come to the right place.

15:59.376 --> 16:00.919
But if you're looking for JB,

16:00.919 --> 16:02.921
it appears he skipped town.

16:04.089 --> 16:05.465
You should've done the same.

16:06.008 --> 16:08.177
[tires screech]
[doors open]

16:09.386 --> 16:11.513
JOE: No-- Hey!
FRANK: Hey! Hey!

16:11.513 --> 16:12.764
JOE: Frank!
FRANK: Joe!

16:12.764 --> 16:15.350
[both struggling]

16:15.350 --> 16:16.852
♪

16:20.314 --> 16:21.523
[gravel flying]

16:21.523 --> 16:24.234
[tires squeal]

16:28.280 --> 16:29.781
WOMAN:
Okay, we're here.

16:29.781 --> 16:31.450
Stop the car and kill the engine.

16:32.492 --> 16:33.744
[brakes squeal]

16:35.746 --> 16:37.748
FENTON: So, is this just
a regular old kidnapping,

16:37.748 --> 16:39.541
or are you going to kill me, too?

16:39.541 --> 16:41.585
WOMAN: I don't know
what you're talking about.

16:41.585 --> 16:43.879
- Your lipstick on that
drinking glass says otherwise.

16:43.879 --> 16:47.132
- McFarlane had information
he believed would keep him alive.

16:47.132 --> 16:48.383
♪

16:48.383 --> 16:49.635
He was wrong.

16:49.635 --> 16:52.179
- So, you're working for
The Circle of the Eye?

16:52.179 --> 16:53.222
WOMAN:
No.

16:53.847 --> 16:56.099
I'm working to destroy them just like you.

16:57.768 --> 17:00.687
That is what you're doing
in Dixon City, isn't it?

17:00.687 --> 17:02.564
Pretending
to fix up your old house

17:02.564 --> 17:05.567
while secretly tracking down
the remaining members of The Circle?

17:06.693 --> 17:08.570
Trying to avenge your wife?

17:09.071 --> 17:10.572
- How long have you been following me?

17:10.572 --> 17:12.908
- Long enough to know
that if you are not careful,

17:12.908 --> 17:15.160
you're going to end up like McFarlane.

17:15.160 --> 17:16.203
Like Laura.

17:17.120 --> 17:19.248
- Who are you?
- I'm curious, Fenton.

17:19.831 --> 17:21.500
If McFarlane had been alive,

17:21.500 --> 17:24.044
what were you willing to do
to get what you wanted?

17:25.045 --> 17:26.588
How far were you willing to go?

17:26.588 --> 17:28.590
♪

17:30.801 --> 17:33.011
[panting]

17:33.011 --> 17:36.098
- So much more efficient
to cut out the middleman, isn't it?

17:36.098 --> 17:39.560
Of course, without JB,
it would have taken us much longer

17:39.560 --> 17:41.478
to focus our efforts on you two.

17:41.478 --> 17:43.564
So, where's The Eye?

17:44.773 --> 17:46.275
- We don't know.

17:46.817 --> 17:48.652
[switch blade opens]
MACK: Answer honestly,

17:48.652 --> 17:50.654
and we can avoid
any unpleasantness.

17:50.654 --> 17:51.989
♪

17:51.989 --> 17:52.990
- Okay.

17:52.990 --> 17:56.076
We'll answer your questions
if you answers ours.

17:56.577 --> 17:58.996
Where's the bomb?
What are you planning?

17:59.538 --> 18:02.666
- No idea. None of your business.

18:02.666 --> 18:05.252
- What'd you do to Dennis?
- Nothing.

18:05.711 --> 18:09.214
See? It's not so hard
to tell the truth.

18:09.214 --> 18:11.717
Now, you try.
ANGELA: Come on, guys.

18:12.384 --> 18:14.219
We know this is a fake.
[clang]

18:14.219 --> 18:17.431
- How could you possibly know that?
ANGELA: Because if it was real,

18:17.431 --> 18:20.184
this little doodad would be lighting up
like a Christmas tree.

18:20.184 --> 18:22.895
- Maybe your doodad's broken.

18:27.608 --> 18:31.028
- It took us a little longer than
I would've liked to get up and running,

18:31.028 --> 18:34.281
but we've locked onto
The Eye's energy signature.

18:34.281 --> 18:36.533
We can trace it remotely.

18:37.034 --> 18:38.660
- So, what do you need us for?

18:38.660 --> 18:41.163
- Yeah, why don't you just
lock on and go get it?

18:41.747 --> 18:44.583
- For some inexplicable reason,

18:44.583 --> 18:47.085
we can only get signal
when The Eye's active.

18:47.085 --> 18:49.880
♪

18:49.880 --> 18:52.382
Like when you used it at
your grandma's house yesterday.

18:54.176 --> 18:56.261
Or the police station this morning.

18:57.179 --> 19:00.015
Did you stash it in
an evidence locker to keep it safe?

19:00.015 --> 19:01.433
- You think an evidence locker is safe?

19:01.433 --> 19:04.561
- [laughs] You're very sure
of yourself, Joe.

19:05.312 --> 19:07.731
I can see why JB likes you.

19:09.149 --> 19:11.485
He thought you hid it on Tom Elroy's farm.

19:12.444 --> 19:14.446
I figured you'd kept it on you.

19:18.617 --> 19:20.619
Guess we were both wrong.

19:26.416 --> 19:27.960
[heavy breathing]

19:31.463 --> 19:32.548
Where's The Eye?

19:33.841 --> 19:35.342
- I told you.

19:36.301 --> 19:37.678
We don't know.

19:39.471 --> 19:40.722
- Suit yourself.

19:42.015 --> 19:45.394
We'll come back a little later
and try this the hard way.

19:50.524 --> 19:53.527
[crowd chatter]

19:58.490 --> 20:01.743
[indistinct murmuring]

20:04.413 --> 20:07.666
- Ow! Watch it!
- Sorry. Hold still.

20:07.666 --> 20:10.669
[overlapping chatter]

20:12.296 --> 20:14.214
KRASSNER: So, you need
teenagers to do your job?

20:14.214 --> 20:16.508
JESSE: No, sir, but they do have
a track record of being right.

20:17.301 --> 20:18.927
- Have you seen the videotape?

20:18.927 --> 20:20.554
- We're still working on it, sir.

20:20.554 --> 20:22.556
- Bring me something concrete
and we'll talk, alright?

20:22.556 --> 20:24.516
In the meantime, keep pressing on Elroy.

20:24.516 --> 20:27.060
♪

20:42.910 --> 20:44.286
[click, creak]

20:57.841 --> 21:00.636
- [sniffs] Anti-freeze.

21:00.636 --> 21:02.554
[crinkling]

21:02.554 --> 21:04.681
Oh my gosh.

21:04.681 --> 21:06.683
- This is the car. Th-this is it.

21:10.312 --> 21:12.606
Come on, come on. Come on.
[opens glove compartment]

21:14.358 --> 21:15.859
Who do you belong to?

21:17.110 --> 21:18.237
Where is it?

21:18.237 --> 21:20.989
♪

21:36.880 --> 21:38.924
FENTON: So, exactly how long are
we going to wait here?

21:38.924 --> 21:40.759
WOMAN:
Just a few more minutes.

21:40.759 --> 21:42.928
I'm still waiting for
an answer to my question.

21:42.928 --> 21:45.514
- [sighs]
I'm not a killer.

21:47.057 --> 21:49.935
You asked what my plan was? Pretty simple.

21:49.935 --> 21:52.521
Identify and expose
all the members of The Circle,

21:53.105 --> 21:54.606
not kill them.

21:55.524 --> 21:58.026
- Don't tell me the idea
didn't cross your mind.

21:59.361 --> 22:00.779
[scoffs]

22:00.779 --> 22:03.782
Regardless, I'm not sure The Circle
will show you the same courtesy.

22:07.286 --> 22:09.079
Cuff yourself to the wheel.
I'll be right back.

22:09.079 --> 22:11.248
- Seriously?
- If you're not willing to kill anyone,

22:11.248 --> 22:12.583
I'm not bringing you up there with me.

22:15.294 --> 22:16.336
[sighs]

22:16.336 --> 22:18.297
Alright, let's go, Fenton.

22:18.297 --> 22:20.299
[zipping]
Both hands.

22:20.299 --> 22:22.509
Nice and tight.
There we go.

22:22.509 --> 22:23.510
[zip]

22:23.510 --> 22:26.471
And I'll take these,
so you don't get any ideas.

22:27.181 --> 22:28.807
Don't go anywhere.
- Yeah.

22:30.475 --> 22:33.478
[shuts car door]
[gate creaks open]

22:33.478 --> 22:36.481
♪

22:42.613 --> 22:44.448
[grunting]

22:50.204 --> 22:51.997
[thud]
[smashing, loud banging]

22:51.997 --> 22:54.499
[man yelling]
[woman panting]

22:57.169 --> 22:59.505
- What'd you do?
- Drive.

22:59.505 --> 23:02.508
- No! I'm not going anywhere
until you tell me what happened up there!

23:02.508 --> 23:03.800
- And what is this?
WOMAN: Go!

23:03.800 --> 23:06.386
Go now!
- No-- On second thought.

23:06.386 --> 23:09.473
[tires squeal]

23:09.473 --> 23:11.517
- Clover McCoy.
- Nope.

23:11.517 --> 23:13.477
- Tony Predo?
- Nope.

23:13.477 --> 23:15.187
- Juna Hayes?
- Nope.

23:15.187 --> 23:18.232
- How is that no one on the senior
track team is taking senior chemistry?

23:18.232 --> 23:19.733
- I think you just answered
your own question.

23:19.733 --> 23:22.194
- Maybe it's not a student.
Maybe it's a teacher or a janitor.

23:22.194 --> 23:24.988
- We'll cross that bridge
when we get to it. Um, Ken Blake?

23:24.988 --> 23:27.366
- No... Nope.
CHET: Coco Jones?

23:28.742 --> 23:30.702
- Donald Dukay?
BIFF: No.

23:30.702 --> 23:31.787
Wait. Yes!

23:31.787 --> 23:33.705
♪

23:33.705 --> 23:35.207
- Seriously?

23:35.749 --> 23:37.543
- Dude, what is that, strawberry?

23:37.543 --> 23:39.586
Dude, what are you, 6?
[car approaching]

23:39.586 --> 23:41.338
You're eating strawberry.
[car doors open]

23:44.049 --> 23:46.593
- Hey, Donald Dukay.
DUKAY: Oh boy, here we go.

23:46.593 --> 23:49.721
What imaginary thing did I do
to ruin your life this time, Kerry?

23:49.721 --> 23:50.722
- Callie!

23:50.722 --> 23:53.433
- Whatever.
- You recognize that voice?

23:53.433 --> 23:56.103
- Yeah, sounds just like the punk
who lit up Tom's house with fireworks.

23:56.103 --> 23:57.771
- No idea what you're talking about.

23:57.771 --> 23:59.231
- Cut the crap, Donald!

23:59.231 --> 24:00.732
Where's the bomb?
What are you planning?

24:02.609 --> 24:04.778
- Okay, now I actually have no idea
what you're talking about.

24:04.778 --> 24:06.947
- It's over, genius.
We know you're the real bomber.

24:06.947 --> 24:08.991
You're on the track team,
you're in chemistry class,

24:08.991 --> 24:10.242
and you had access to fireworks.

24:10.242 --> 24:12.077
- Tell us where the bomb is
so we can tell the cops.

24:12.077 --> 24:13.662
- You think I have a bomb?

24:13.662 --> 24:15.163
[scoffs] Why?

24:15.706 --> 24:17.875
Because I like to mess
with the Widowmaker?

24:17.875 --> 24:20.460
Because I like to shoot off fireworks?

24:20.460 --> 24:21.879
Can I go enjoy Demon Day now,

24:21.879 --> 24:24.214
or do you guys want
to keep being weird at me?

24:24.214 --> 24:25.632
♪

24:25.632 --> 24:27.968
- You have a blue car.
DUKAY: So what?

24:27.968 --> 24:30.470
Do you know how many
people have blue cars?

24:30.470 --> 24:32.264
My-my-my cousin has a blue car.

24:32.264 --> 24:34.349
My ex-girlfriend has a blue car.

24:34.349 --> 24:37.060
Hey, why don't you go ask her
if she's the bomber?

24:37.060 --> 24:39.938
While you're at it, you can ask her
for my track jacket back, okay?

24:39.938 --> 24:42.191
- Your ex-girlfriend
has your track jacket.

24:42.983 --> 24:45.527
- Yeah. She never gave it back
when we broke up.

24:45.527 --> 24:47.237
She's a little crazy. It was fun at first,

24:47.237 --> 24:48.864
but it's kind of why I dumped her.

24:48.864 --> 24:50.532
- Who is she, Donald?!

24:51.575 --> 24:53.994
- Vanessa Bender.

24:53.994 --> 24:56.538
[quiet chatter]

24:56.538 --> 24:59.499
- Well, Vanessa,
you look absolutely stunning,

24:59.499 --> 25:01.376
if I do say so myself.

25:01.376 --> 25:02.878
Enjoy your big moment.

25:03.629 --> 25:06.048
- Totally.
It's going to be a blast.

25:06.048 --> 25:07.925
♪

25:09.927 --> 25:12.930
[engine rumbling]
[tires squeal]

25:16.225 --> 25:18.727
[scraping gravel]

25:19.394 --> 25:20.395
[engine stops]

25:20.395 --> 25:22.189
WOMAN:
Hey. [sighs]

25:22.189 --> 25:23.982
[doors shut]
What are you doing?

25:23.982 --> 25:25.400
Get back in the car.
- No.

25:25.943 --> 25:27.736
We lost the shooters.
I'm not going anywhere

25:27.736 --> 25:29.738
until you tell me what is it
you stole from them?

25:30.531 --> 25:33.534
You know, I don't mind gettin' shot at--
- You don't mind being shot at?

25:33.534 --> 25:35.369
- I usually have an idea why.

25:35.369 --> 25:37.746
- You'll get answers soon enough.
Get back in the car, Fenton.

25:37.746 --> 25:40.249
- [laughs] Or what? What are you gonna do?

25:40.249 --> 25:42.084
You gonna shoot me?
You'd have done it by now.

25:42.084 --> 25:43.502
[bang]
[Fenton grunts]

25:43.502 --> 25:45.838
- Hey. You don't mind, do you?

25:46.839 --> 25:48.215
Next one will be an inch to the left.

25:48.215 --> 25:51.218
♪

25:51.218 --> 25:52.886
- Who are you?

25:54.346 --> 25:56.598
- My name is Olivia Kowalski.

25:57.808 --> 25:59.935
- Your mother's Anya Kowalski.

25:59.935 --> 26:00.978
The fortune teller.

26:02.020 --> 26:04.898
- Fortune tellers
are a sideshow act at carnivals.

26:04.898 --> 26:06.191
My mother has a gift.

26:06.942 --> 26:09.945
In fact, your boys went to her
for help with a case, didn't they?

26:10.529 --> 26:13.365
- Keep my family out of it.
- Circle of the Eye didn't.

26:13.907 --> 26:16.493
They destroyed both our families, Fenton.

26:16.493 --> 26:17.911
We have a chance for revenge.
[Fenton sighs]

26:17.911 --> 26:19.788
- I want justice.

26:19.788 --> 26:21.874
- Keep telling yourself that.

26:22.749 --> 26:24.126
With Gloria Estabrook in jail,

26:24.126 --> 26:26.587
The Circle is vulnerable
for the first time in years.

26:26.587 --> 26:30.007
But we have to move fast because
someone else is vying for control.

26:30.007 --> 26:31.341
[sighs]

26:31.341 --> 26:33.677
You know this.
- Yeah.

26:33.677 --> 26:35.512
- It's the same person
who ordered Laura's death.

26:37.931 --> 26:39.349
- Do you have their name?

26:40.017 --> 26:41.727
- That's why you hunted down McFarlane,
isn't it?

26:41.727 --> 26:43.520
- Give me their name.

26:45.022 --> 26:47.524
- First, I need something from you.
- What?

26:48.650 --> 26:50.652
- Your trust.
[Fenton scoffs]

26:50.652 --> 26:52.237
- Meet me tomorrow at the Grand Hotel.

26:52.237 --> 26:54.698
[car approaching]

26:56.033 --> 26:58.368
- Why don't you just give me
the information now?

26:59.703 --> 27:01.413
- 'Cause I have a little more work to do.

27:01.413 --> 27:04.416
♪

27:06.710 --> 27:09.713
[car door shuts]
[car speeds off]

27:13.342 --> 27:15.719
- Where's Vanessa Bender?!
- On the float, why?

27:15.719 --> 27:16.803
- We think she's the real bomber.

27:16.803 --> 27:19.056
- What? Why do you think that?

27:19.056 --> 27:20.682
- She's got a blue car,
she's in chemistry class,

27:20.682 --> 27:22.267
and she was wearing
her ex-boyfriend's track jacket.

27:23.018 --> 27:25.687
- "It's going to be a blast."
Oh, that little...

27:25.687 --> 27:26.772
- Where's the float now?

27:26.772 --> 27:29.775
♪ tense music ♪

27:29.775 --> 27:31.276
[paper crinkling]

27:32.444 --> 27:34.655
TRUDY: The parade starts here,
goes down Spruce,

27:34.655 --> 27:37.074
cuts across Tradition,
then on to Main,

27:37.074 --> 27:40.244
across Seven, back on to Main,
and goes all the way down to the water.

27:40.244 --> 27:42.663
If I had to guess,
I'd say Vanessa is about to hit Main.

27:46.375 --> 27:47.376
What?

27:47.376 --> 27:49.253
What are you staring at?

27:49.253 --> 27:50.796
- It's a lightning bolt.

27:50.796 --> 27:52.381
- Dennis must've seen
Vanessa draw it on the map.

27:52.381 --> 27:54.216
- The bomb isn't gonna be
at the fireworks show.

27:54.216 --> 27:56.343
It's somewhere on the parade route.
- Not somewhere.

27:56.343 --> 27:57.386
Here.

27:58.303 --> 28:00.347
That's Dennis' drawing.
CALLIE: What's in that radius?

28:00.347 --> 28:02.891
- Uh, shops, restaurants, uh,

28:02.891 --> 28:04.560
a law office, an alarm company...

28:04.560 --> 28:07.437
- Wilt's. Wilt's. It's got to be Wilt's.
He got broken into the other night.

28:07.437 --> 28:09.147
We thought of some stupid
Demon Week prank,

28:09.147 --> 28:10.941
but nothing was stolen.

28:10.941 --> 28:12.276
What if something was left behind?

28:12.276 --> 28:14.695
- I'm going to call him to warn him.
- We've gotta go after Vanessa.

28:14.695 --> 28:16.405
- First, we call your mom,
then we go after Vanessa.

28:16.405 --> 28:18.073
Come on, come on, Biff.

28:18.073 --> 28:20.784
- Where's Phil?
- Where are Frank and Joe?

28:20.784 --> 28:23.161
[struggling]

28:23.161 --> 28:24.371
[panting]

28:24.371 --> 28:27.082
[clanging]

28:27.082 --> 28:28.792
- Can you stop?

28:28.792 --> 28:30.794
- Just-- I almost got it. [groans]

28:32.588 --> 28:34.089
[clanging]

28:35.007 --> 28:37.718
[sighs] Okay.

28:37.718 --> 28:39.469
The way I see it,

28:39.469 --> 28:41.138
our best option is...

28:41.138 --> 28:43.515
someone gets close enough to head butt.

28:44.433 --> 28:46.393
- And then what?
- I gotta think of everything?

28:46.393 --> 28:49.062
- Joe!
It doesn't matter. If we break free,

28:49.062 --> 28:50.939
who knows how many Stratemeyer
goons are out there?

28:50.939 --> 28:52.649
- What are they gonna do?
Keep us down here forever?

28:52.649 --> 28:54.776
- No, I'm sure they'll kill us eventually.

28:54.776 --> 28:55.777
[sighs]

28:58.447 --> 29:00.449
- You know, I'm starting to think
she wasn't bluffing.

29:01.366 --> 29:02.993
That they really can track The Eye.

29:05.537 --> 29:07.039
- Yeah, me, too.

29:08.207 --> 29:10.375
- We're sitting ducks down here.

29:10.375 --> 29:12.377
What if you have another one of your--
- [whispers]: Joe.

29:13.378 --> 29:14.796
They could be listening.

29:14.796 --> 29:16.965
- [whispers]: Panic attacks?

29:16.965 --> 29:18.217
I was going to say panic attacks.

29:18.217 --> 29:20.511
- Well, it's a good thing
there's nothing to panic about.

29:20.511 --> 29:23.514
♪ marching band ♪

29:23.514 --> 29:25.807
[crowd cheering]

29:25.807 --> 29:27.559
[clapping]

29:36.527 --> 29:38.153
[muffled music, cheering]

29:38.153 --> 29:39.947
- Oh, my head...

29:40.489 --> 29:41.490
[sighs]

29:44.451 --> 29:46.495
Oh my god. Oh my god.
I'm in the trunk.

29:46.495 --> 29:49.414
Help! Help!
[banging]

29:49.414 --> 29:50.749
I'm in the trunk! Help!

29:50.749 --> 29:53.043
♪ marching band blaring ♪

29:53.043 --> 29:55.921
[crowd cheering]

30:01.677 --> 30:04.221
[panting]
- Since when do you pick locks?

30:04.221 --> 30:05.889
- I've been hanging out with
Frank and Joe for too long.

30:05.889 --> 30:07.766
- Or just the right amount.
CALLIE: Okay, come on.

30:07.766 --> 30:09.601
We gotta check everywhere.
It's been two days, and no one's seen it.

30:09.601 --> 30:11.562
- I'll check behind the counter.
- I'll start back here.

30:11.562 --> 30:12.563
- I'll clear the shelves.

30:12.563 --> 30:15.107
Don't forget the freezers.
The bomb could be tucked anywhere.

30:15.107 --> 30:18.652
♪ muffled marching band ♪

30:18.652 --> 30:22.072
[panting, rummaging]

30:22.072 --> 30:23.782
- Guys, it was... it was moved.

30:23.782 --> 30:26.159
- What?
CHET: Robowar.

30:27.035 --> 30:29.538
It was moved. I helped Frank move it back
against the wall and plug it in.

30:29.538 --> 30:32.040
[heavy breathing]

30:32.040 --> 30:34.543
- You think the bomb's inside the game?

30:38.422 --> 30:40.549
- There's only one way to find out.

30:40.549 --> 30:43.927
♪ marching band blaring ♪

30:43.927 --> 30:46.930
[crowd cheering]

30:51.310 --> 30:53.103
♪ muffled marching band ♪

30:53.103 --> 30:55.439
[beeping]
- Oh my god.

30:55.439 --> 30:58.192
♪

30:58.192 --> 31:00.319
- We should call the police.
JESSE: Don't touch it.

31:00.319 --> 31:01.945
Don't do anything
except get the hell outta here.

31:04.573 --> 31:06.867
Riley, it's Chief Hooper.

31:06.867 --> 31:08.410
I've got an IED at Wilt's.

31:08.410 --> 31:11.371
No timer.
Trigger's a garage door opener.

31:11.371 --> 31:14.333
I need DCPD Bomb Squad
on my radio right now.

31:14.333 --> 31:16.585
[radio static]
RILEY [on radio]: Copy that, Chief.

31:16.585 --> 31:18.962
- Vanessa must have the detonator.
She's getting closer every second.

31:18.962 --> 31:20.797
- I need your help.
Clear the area outside.

31:20.797 --> 31:23.592
Get those people out of here.
- Okay. Go. Go, go. Come on. Let's go.

31:23.592 --> 31:26.345
- Move! Move! Move!
- Get back! Get back! Come on!

31:26.345 --> 31:28.639
[all shouting]

31:28.639 --> 31:31.642
♪ marching band blaring ♪

31:31.642 --> 31:34.228
[muffled shouting]

31:35.437 --> 31:37.272
♪

31:37.272 --> 31:38.190
- What are you doing?!

31:38.190 --> 31:40.526
- My job! Go!

31:43.320 --> 31:46.657
♪ marching band ♪

31:47.282 --> 31:49.743
- Everybody, get back!
Get back! Clear the area!

31:49.743 --> 31:51.161
There's a bomb! Everybody!

31:51.161 --> 31:52.913
I need you to listen!

31:52.913 --> 31:54.623
There is a bomb that is about to go off!

31:54.623 --> 31:56.708
[tires screech]
- Ah!

31:56.708 --> 31:58.210
- Vanessa Bender, don't you move!

31:58.210 --> 32:00.420
♪

32:00.420 --> 32:02.339
[sword clatters]

32:07.219 --> 32:08.762
[both grunt]

32:08.762 --> 32:11.014
[struggling]
Stay down.

32:12.516 --> 32:16.019
- Nice hit.
- Yeah. Congrats to me.

32:16.019 --> 32:17.771
Check her for a detonator.

32:17.771 --> 32:19.731
- [giggles] You're too late.

32:21.066 --> 32:22.985
[muffled crowd chatter]

32:23.318 --> 32:24.570
PHIL:
Lola...

32:24.570 --> 32:25.779
[thud]

32:27.072 --> 32:28.949
Give me that! Stop!

32:30.075 --> 32:32.786
Don't!
[both struggle]

32:32.786 --> 32:34.663
BOMB SQUAD: Okay, Chief.
I'm gonna talk you through this.

32:34.663 --> 32:37.916
You're going to need
to disconnect the detonator

32:37.916 --> 32:39.042
from the power supply.

32:39.042 --> 32:40.794
- No, no, no.

32:40.794 --> 32:43.005
[both struggling]
Stop...

32:44.214 --> 32:45.841
Don't!
[click]

32:45.841 --> 32:47.718
No!
[beep, fizzling]

32:47.718 --> 32:49.887
[high-pitched whirring]

32:49.887 --> 32:52.848
[explosion]
[crowd screaming]

32:52.848 --> 32:55.851
[alarm blaring]

32:58.896 --> 33:00.439
[door opens]

33:00.439 --> 33:03.192
[machine beeping weakly]

33:03.192 --> 33:04.985
- Last chance, boys.

33:04.985 --> 33:07.613
- Okay, we'll tell you everything.

33:07.613 --> 33:09.865
[beeping stops]
Just... come a little closer.

33:11.700 --> 33:12.701
[sighs]

33:12.701 --> 33:15.370
- Where... is... The Eye?

33:15.370 --> 33:17.497
- I told you, we don't know where it is.

33:17.497 --> 33:18.999
- Stop. Lying.

33:21.001 --> 33:22.169
You know where it is, Frank.

33:22.169 --> 33:23.670
♪

33:23.670 --> 33:25.297
YOUNG GEORGE:
You know where it is, Frank.

33:25.297 --> 33:27.341
[high-pitched ringing]
[heavy breathing]

33:27.341 --> 33:29.760
- No! [gasps]

33:29.760 --> 33:32.137
ANGELA:
[laughs] Relax, Frank.

33:32.137 --> 33:34.515
We haven't even started the hard way yet.

33:35.265 --> 33:38.227
[beeping]

33:38.227 --> 33:40.187
Huh.
[door opens]

33:40.187 --> 33:42.814
♪

33:42.814 --> 33:44.733
[beeping continues]

33:46.360 --> 33:47.819
[whispering]

33:49.905 --> 33:52.115
[heavy breathing]

33:54.910 --> 33:56.161
You're free to go.

33:58.497 --> 34:01.458
There was an incident in town.
A bomb went off at Wilt's.

34:01.458 --> 34:05.045
- Was anybody hurt? Did-did--
ANGELA: I don't have those details,

34:05.045 --> 34:08.131
and I don't want to add to the confusion
by keeping you two here.

34:08.131 --> 34:09.550
Go. Now.

34:09.550 --> 34:12.386
[beeping continues]

34:12.386 --> 34:14.388
- What, we're supposed to
just forget about all this?

34:14.388 --> 34:17.558
- I'm sure our paths will cross again.

34:17.558 --> 34:20.018
Until then, I'm going to notify the police

34:20.018 --> 34:23.063
that two nosy teenagers were
trespassing on private property

34:23.063 --> 34:25.274
and were detained for security reasons.

34:25.274 --> 34:28.735
Just to avoid any misunderstandings.

34:30.404 --> 34:33.448
[beeping continues]

34:33.907 --> 34:35.284
[grunts]

34:35.284 --> 34:38.287
♪

34:38.287 --> 34:40.581
[beeping continues]

34:43.584 --> 34:46.587
[panting]

34:48.046 --> 34:51.216
- What the hell was that? You okay?

34:51.216 --> 34:54.136
- Yeah, I am for now.
The tracker works. She got a signal.

34:54.136 --> 34:56.471
- Why'd she let us go?

34:56.471 --> 34:58.640
- Because it wasn't coming from me.

34:58.640 --> 35:00.267
It was coming from somewhere else.

35:01.685 --> 35:02.811
- Come on.

35:03.604 --> 35:05.898
[alarm blaring]

35:05.898 --> 35:08.901
[panicked chatter]

35:08.901 --> 35:10.736
- Did Jesse get out?
- I don't know!

35:10.736 --> 35:13.739
[panting]

35:14.406 --> 35:16.408
- [gasps] Jesse.

35:17.326 --> 35:18.660
[alarm blaring]

35:18.660 --> 35:20.871
Jesse?!
[Riley muttering]

35:20.871 --> 35:22.956
[electricity crackling, popping]
[yelps]

35:22.956 --> 35:25.459
RILEY: She's over here!
[gasping]

35:26.084 --> 35:28.003
- Is she...
- She's alive.

35:28.003 --> 35:29.546
It looks like she took cover just in time.

35:29.546 --> 35:31.840
The counter saved her.
OFFICER [radio]: What do you need, Deputy?

35:31.840 --> 35:34.551
- She needs an ambulance.
OFFICER: Copy. There's one en route.

35:34.551 --> 35:36.428
- Come on, what's the ETA
on the ambulance?

35:36.428 --> 35:38.722
OFFICER: Minutes away.
RILEY: Stay with us, Jesse. Stay with us.

35:38.722 --> 35:41.558
[alarm ringing]
PHIL: Chet! Belinda!

35:41.558 --> 35:44.394
It's Lola! It's Lola Burton!

35:44.394 --> 35:46.438
- No, no, no, it's Vanessa.
- No, no, no. It's Vanessa's car,

35:46.438 --> 35:48.774
but Lola was driving it. She had
the detonator and I tried to stop her,

35:48.774 --> 35:50.234
but she got away.
She has a mask and a cloak.

35:50.234 --> 35:51.735
She has to be here somewhere. I...

35:51.735 --> 35:54.279
[crowd chatter]
[alarm ringing]

35:56.114 --> 35:58.492
♪ dramatic music ♪

35:58.492 --> 35:59.910
- Lola! Lola, stop!

36:03.413 --> 36:04.665
Go get the cops! Go get the cops!

36:04.665 --> 36:07.209
♪

36:09.253 --> 36:11.630
[distant siren]
[panting]

36:20.889 --> 36:23.183
[panting]

36:26.019 --> 36:28.522
[panting]
[distant siren]

36:30.190 --> 36:32.276
LOLA: Get your hands off me!
- It's over, Lola.

36:32.276 --> 36:34.111
BELINDA:
There's nowhere to run.

36:34.111 --> 36:37.114
[panting]

36:37.114 --> 36:39.408
- Nice timing, guys.
JOE: Thanks.

36:39.408 --> 36:41.660
Saw you guys a few blocks back.
We pieced it together.

36:41.660 --> 36:44.496
- Let's catch up later.
I want to know why she did it.

36:44.496 --> 36:46.373
- Go to hell.
- You could've killed someone!

36:46.373 --> 36:49.168
- The explosion wasn't
supposed to be so big.

36:49.168 --> 36:51.044
Vanessa must have messed with it
without me knowing.

36:51.044 --> 36:52.838
No one was supposed to get hurt.
JOE: Oh yeah?

36:52.838 --> 36:55.299
What about Dennis?
- I didn't do anything to Dennis.

36:55.299 --> 36:57.801
- Oh, I suppose that was Vanessa, too?
How convenient.

36:57.801 --> 37:01.054
- It wasn't her, either!
I swear we didn't do anything to Dennis!

37:01.054 --> 37:04.349
- Dennis caught you and Vanessa
on tape planning the attack.

37:04.349 --> 37:05.726
You chased him through the woods!

37:05.726 --> 37:07.269
[siren wailing]
[panting]

37:07.269 --> 37:09.188
- We chased him, we didn't hurt him.

37:09.188 --> 37:11.148
He was fine when we handed him over.

37:11.148 --> 37:14.151
We just wanted the money.
JOE: Wait, handed him over to who?

37:14.151 --> 37:15.944
- Nope! No, no.

37:15.944 --> 37:18.739
FRANK: What money?
[panting]

37:18.739 --> 37:21.074
What money?!
[handcuffs clicking]

37:22.242 --> 37:23.327
Lola!

37:23.327 --> 37:26.371
♪

37:26.371 --> 37:29.166
[gurney rattling]

37:31.210 --> 37:32.252
- Mom?

37:32.252 --> 37:35.881
Mom! Mom, can you hear me?

37:35.881 --> 37:37.132
Mom?

37:38.550 --> 37:41.220
Mom? Mom!
- Hey, hey, it's okay, it's okay...

37:42.304 --> 37:45.599
It's okay, I got you. Biff, I'm here.
Everything will be alright.

37:45.599 --> 37:48.602
[sirens wailing]
[police radio chatter]

37:55.067 --> 37:58.070
[ventilator hissing]
[indistinct PA announcement]

38:01.073 --> 38:02.699
- She's going to pull through.

38:04.785 --> 38:06.370
- What if she doesn't?

38:08.205 --> 38:10.332
I don't have anyone else.

38:10.332 --> 38:12.042
- Yes, you do.

38:12.042 --> 38:13.710
♪

38:13.710 --> 38:15.212
Your mom's a fighter,

38:16.463 --> 38:17.965
and she's still mad at us.

38:19.383 --> 38:21.885
No way she passes up
a chance to lay down the law.

38:24.179 --> 38:25.764
Let it out, Biff. I'm right here.

38:26.473 --> 38:29.476
[crying]

38:29.476 --> 38:32.479
[ventilator hissing]
[machines beeping]

38:38.902 --> 38:42.614
[on PA]: Thoracic surgery, call 156.
Thoracic surgery, 156, please.

38:43.198 --> 38:45.075
KRASSNER [quietly]:
Alright, Deputy, let's make this quick.

38:45.075 --> 38:47.202
There's a lot going on,
and we need to get our stories straight.

38:47.202 --> 38:48.620
What have you got?

38:49.997 --> 38:52.124
- [quietly]: Tom Elroy's been released.
He's not going to sue.

38:52.124 --> 38:53.792
- Oh, finally, some good news.

38:53.792 --> 38:56.962
- The girls confessed, but they're
claiming they never hurt the Gilroy kid.

38:56.962 --> 38:59.131
That someone paid them
to do the bombing.

38:59.131 --> 39:00.382
- Did they say who?
- No.

39:00.382 --> 39:02.342
Never saw a face.
KRASSNER: Are they sure?

39:02.342 --> 39:05.762
RILEY: Yeah. Whoever it is wore
a demon's mask, used a voice changer.

39:06.138 --> 39:08.307
- Alright, let's, uh, keep this quiet.

39:08.307 --> 39:10.601
As far as anyone knows,
the girls did it alone.

39:10.601 --> 39:13.061
Can't have people thinking
there's a maniac on the loose.

39:13.061 --> 39:14.146
- Yeah.

39:14.146 --> 39:17.149
♪

39:22.404 --> 39:23.614
[insects chirping]

39:23.614 --> 39:25.240
BELINDA:
Wild day, huh?

39:27.201 --> 39:28.702
You alright?

39:31.079 --> 39:32.706
- Yeah. I mean...

39:33.999 --> 39:36.793
Here I thought my life got crazy
when the Hardy Boys came to town, but...

39:37.878 --> 39:40.881
things seem to have gotten to a whole
new level since you've been here.

39:40.881 --> 39:42.549
♪

39:42.549 --> 39:44.384
- Do you want me to leave?

39:45.469 --> 39:46.470
- No.

39:48.347 --> 39:49.932
I want you to stay for good.

39:52.226 --> 39:53.227
[quiet laugh]

39:55.521 --> 39:58.524
♪

39:58.524 --> 40:01.527
[quiet chatter]

40:04.238 --> 40:05.239
[siren wails]

40:05.239 --> 40:07.741
- Something about all this
still doesn't feel right.

40:08.867 --> 40:10.369
This was bigger than a bombing.

40:14.998 --> 40:17.000
- We need to talk about our fight.

40:18.418 --> 40:20.045
- I was wrong.

40:21.922 --> 40:23.882
And I'm sorry.

40:24.424 --> 40:27.135
I don't care that you went
to go see my grandma.

40:27.135 --> 40:29.096
I mean, after today,
it feels like such a small thing

40:29.096 --> 40:30.889
when we could have
lost each other.

40:34.142 --> 40:35.769
I don't want to lose you.

40:36.979 --> 40:38.981
And I don't want us
lying to each other.

40:41.733 --> 40:43.068
Or keeping secrets.

40:45.946 --> 40:48.115
There's something that I need to tell you.

40:49.116 --> 40:50.909
Something really strange.

40:52.494 --> 40:53.745
- What is it?

40:55.956 --> 40:57.416
♪

40:57.416 --> 41:00.878
[video game beeping]

41:00.878 --> 41:02.838
LAURA:
Capture as many gems as you can.

41:02.838 --> 41:04.631
[eerie noises]

41:04.631 --> 41:06.175
[fire crackling]

41:06.967 --> 41:08.343
There's one very special one.

41:08.343 --> 41:09.845
[distortion]

41:11.513 --> 41:13.098
[rumbling]

41:14.600 --> 41:16.185
[thud]
[Frank gasps]

41:16.185 --> 41:17.936
- Frank, what is it?

41:17.936 --> 41:19.104
- This is just the beginning.

41:21.023 --> 41:22.524
Something worse is coming.

41:23.692 --> 41:26.695
♪
